<subSubSection id="3796656070D6FF30FF23ED2E8E72FADA" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="7F3336EB70D6FF30FF23ED2E8E72FADA" blockId="168.[151,1436,855,1312]" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D6FF30FF23ED2E8B44FC51" bold="true" box="[199,335,891,916]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" reason="1">Comments.</emphasis>
This species was moved from 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D6FF30FD52ED29893CFC51" authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1855" box="[694,823,892,916]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Hypoclinea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D6FF30FD52ED29893CFC51" box="[694,823,892,916]" italics="true" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">Hypoclinea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D6FF30FC84ED298E05FC51" authorityName="Emery" authorityYear="1869" box="[864,1038,892,916]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Bothriomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D6FF30FC84ED298E05FC51" box="[864,1038,892,916]" italics="true" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">Bothriomyrmex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="1B1D4B1A70D6FF30FBD8ED298F19FC51" author="Dalla Torre, C. G. de" box="[1084,1298,892,916]" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" refId="ref110399" refString="Dalla Torre, C. G. de (1893) Catalogus hymenopterorum hucusque descriptorum systematicus et synonymicus. Vol. 7 Formicidae (Heterogyna). Leipzig: G. Engelmann, 289 pp." type="book" year="1893">Dalla Torre (1893)</bibRefCitation>
and then to 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D6FF30FF73EDF58B23FC7D" baseAuthorityName="Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="1990" box="[151,296,928,952]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Iridomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D6FF30FF73EDF58B23FC7D" box="[151,296,928,952]" italics="true" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">Iridomyrmex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="1B1D4B1A70D6FF30FEB7EDCA881FFC72" author="Wheeler, W. M." box="[339,532,927,951]" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" pagination="1 - 142" refId="ref113081" refString="Wheeler, W. M. (1915 b) The ants of the Baltic Amber. Schriften der Physikalisch-okonomischen Gesellschaft zu Konigsberg in Pr., 55 (1914), 1 - 142." type="journal article" year="1915">Wheeler (1915b)</bibRefCitation>
, a position supported by 
<bibRefCitation id="1B1D4B1A70D6FF30FCD5EDCA89FAFC72" author="Shattuck, S. O." box="[817,1009,927,951]" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" pagination="13 - 18" refId="ref112320" refString="Shattuck, S. O. (1992 a) Review of the dolichoderine ant genus Iridomyrme x Mayr with descriptions of three new genera (Hymenoptera: Formicidae). Journal of the Australian Entomological Society, 31, 13 - 18." type="journal article" year="1992">
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D6FF30FCD5EDCA8998FC72" authority="Heterick &amp; Shattuck, 2011" authorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" authorityYear="2011" box="[817,915,927,951]" genus="Shattuck" pageId="168" pageNumber="170" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">Shattuck</taxonomicName>
(1992a)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="1B1D4B1A70D6FF30FBCDEDCA8ED0FC72" author="Dlussky, G. M." box="[1065,1243,927,951]" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" pagination="616 - 627" refId="ref110477" refString="Dlussky, G. M. (1997) Genera of ants from Baltic Amber. Paleontological Journal, 31 (6), 616 - 627." type="journal article" year="1997">Dlussky (1997)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="1B1D4B1A70D6FF30FB02EDCA8F9CFC72" author="Dlussky, G. M." box="[1254,1431,927,951]" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" pagination="616 - 627" refId="ref110477" refString="Dlussky, G. M. (1997) Genera of ants from Baltic Amber. Paleontological Journal, 31 (6), 616 - 627." type="journal article" year="1997">Dlussky (1997)</bibRefCitation>
, in a study of Baltic amber ants, provides a key to genera of ants occurring in this amber, where he states that the anterior margin of the clypeus in 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D6FF30FDECEDBD8892FBC5" baseAuthorityName="Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="1990" box="[520,665,1000,1024]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Iridomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D6FF30FDECEDBD8892FBC5" box="[520,665,1000,1024]" italics="true" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">Iridomyrmex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a “small medial lobe projecting forwards”. However, his illustration of the head of 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D6FF30FE8DEA588BD5FBE1" authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1868" box="[361,478,1037,1060]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Hypoclinea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geinitzi">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D6FF30FE8DEA588BD5FBE1" box="[361,478,1037,1060]" italics="true" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">H. geinitzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(fig. 2e) clearly shows the anterior clypeal margin as being uniformly convex and not with the anteromedial clypeal prominence characteristic of typical 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D6FF30FC6AEA658E15FB8D" baseAuthorityName="Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="1990" box="[910,1054,1072,1096]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Iridomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D6FF30FC6AEA658E15FB8D" box="[910,1054,1072,1096]" italics="true" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">Iridomyrmex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Additionally, the eyes (based on fig. 2e) are placed more anteriorly and laterally on the head compared to extant 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D6FF30FBFFEA018EA7FBA9" baseAuthorityName="Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="1990" box="[1051,1196,1108,1132]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Iridomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D6FF30FBFFEA018EA7FBA9" box="[1051,1196,1108,1132]" italics="true" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">Iridomyrmex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, where they are typically positioned more medially and posteriorly. It seems clear that this species does not belong to 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D6FF30FB3EEA2D8F60FB55" baseAuthorityName="Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="1990" box="[1242,1387,1144,1168]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Iridomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D6FF30FB3EEA2D8F60FB55" box="[1242,1387,1144,1168]" italics="true" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">Iridomyrmex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but rather to 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D6FF30FEE5EAC98BB4FB71" authorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[257,447,1180,1204]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Anonychomyrma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D6FF30FEE5EAC98BB4FB71" box="[257,447,1180,1204]" italics="true" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">Anonychomyrma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as the head is typical of that genus. The body (based on 
<bibRefCitation id="1B1D4B1A70D6FF30FBBBEAC98F2AFB71" author="Dlussky, G. M." box="[1119,1313,1180,1204]" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" pagination="616 - 627" refId="ref110477" refString="Dlussky, G. M. (1997) Genera of ants from Baltic Amber. Paleontological Journal, 31 (6), 616 - 627." type="journal article" year="1997">Dlussky’s (1997)</bibRefCitation>
fig. 2d) is slightly more elongate than typical extant 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D6FF30FD88EA958921FB1D" authorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[620,810,1216,1240]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Anonychomyrma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D6FF30FD88EA958921FB1D" box="[620,810,1216,1240]" italics="true" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">Anonychomyrma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but not unduly and approaches the morphology seen in some 
<collectingRegion id="BD48F80970D6FF30FF3DEAB18B16FB3E" box="[217,285,1252,1275]" country="Indonesia" name="Papua Barat" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">Papua</collectingRegion>
New Guinean species of the genus. Because of this, this species is here transferred from 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D6FF30FAEFEAB18F97FB39" baseAuthorityName="Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="1990" box="[1291,1436,1252,1276]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Iridomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D6FF30FAEFEAB18F97FB39" box="[1291,1436,1252,1276]" italics="true" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">Iridomyrmex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D6FF30FF50EB5D8B79FAE5" authorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[180,370,1288,1312]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Anonychomyrma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D6FF30FF50EB5D8B79FAE5" box="[180,370,1288,1312]" italics="true" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">Anonychomyrma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(noting the geographic distribution of the genus as discussed above).
</paragraph>
